xxhsum 0.8.3 (Crystal implementation)
Create or verify checksums using fast non-cryptographic algorithm xxHash

Usage: xxhsum [options] [FILES...]

When no filename provided or when '-' is provided, uses stdin as input.

Options:
    -H#                              select an xxhash algorithm (default: 1)
                                       0: XXH32
                                       1: XXH64
                                       2: XXH128 (also called XXH3_128bits)
                                       3: XXH3 (also called XXH3_64bits)
    -c, --check                      read xxHash checksum from [FILES] and check them
    --filelist                       (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED) generate hashes for files listed in [FILES]
    -h, --help                       display this help message

Advanced:
    -V, --version                    Display version information
    --tag                            Produce BSD-style checksum lines
    --little-endian                  (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED) Checksum values use little endian convention (default: big endian)
    --binary                         (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED) Read in binary mode
    -b                               Run benchmark
    -b#                              Bench only algorithm variant #
    -i#                              Number of times to run the benchmark (default: 3)
    -B#                              Benchmark sample size (supports K,KB,M,MB,G,GB â€” 1024-based)
    -q, --quiet                      Don't display version header in benchmark mode

File list options:
    --status                         (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED) Don't output anything, status code shows success
    --strict                         Exit non-zero for improperly formatted lines in [FILES]
    --warn                           (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED) Warn about improperly formatted lines in [FILES]
    --ignore-missing                 Don't fail or report status for missing files
    -s SEED, --seed SEED             Seed (decimal or 0xHEX)
    --bench-all                      Run all 28 benchmark variants (equivalent to -b0)
